</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Calling signal.</emphasis>
In poplar-feeding 
<taxonomicName box="[607,724,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,724,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Macropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species no clear-cut distinction exists between calling and courtship signals. 
<collectingCountry box="[355,386,476,500]" name="American Samoa" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">As</collectingCountry>
a rule, single male produces simple signal (calling in the strict sense), but occasionally it can produce more complex signal containing additional components. Courting male sitting close to female produces only complex signal.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227530/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" targetBox="[174,1423,625,1890]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1912,1996]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,343,1912,1935]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">FIGURES 37–46.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Dubovsky" authorityName="Dubovsky" box="[352,706,1913,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="validiuscula">
<emphasis box="[352,591,1913,1935]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Macropsis validiuscula</emphasis>
Dubovsky
</taxonomicName>
, oscillograms of male calling signals. 37–38, 40–42―simple form of calling signal, 39, 43–46―complex form. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “40–46” are given under the same numbers.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,722]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">
Simple calling of 
<taxonomicName box="[404,580,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="validiuscula">
<emphasis box="[404,580,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">M. validiuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a phrase lasting from 
<number box="[865,931,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="5.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="2.0">2 to 8</number>
– 
<number box="[947,975,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="10.0">10</number>
s (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1238,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 46" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[174,1423,625,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,625,1892]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 46. Macropsis validiuscula Dubovsky, oscillograms of male calling signals. 37 – 38, 40 – 42 ― simple form of calling signal, 39, 43 – 46 ― complex form. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “ 40 – 46 ” are given under the same numbers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227530/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">
Figs. 
<number box="[1077,1192,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="37.7" valueMax="38.4" valueMin="37.0">37–38, 40</number>
– 
<number box="[1208,1238,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
). Complex signal (
<figureCitation box="[159,345,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 46" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[174,1423,625,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,625,1892]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 46. Macropsis validiuscula Dubovsky, oscillograms of male calling signals. 37 – 38, 40 – 42 ― simple form of calling signal, 39, 43 – 46 ― complex form. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “ 40 – 46 ” are given under the same numbers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227530/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">
Figs. 
<number box="[227,345,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="42.715" valueMax="46.0" valueMin="39.43">39, 43–46</number>
</figureCitation>
) consists of the same phrase as a simple one (
<figureCitation box="[904,1046,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 46" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[174,1423,625,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,625,1892]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 46. Macropsis validiuscula Dubovsky, oscillograms of male calling signals. 37 – 38, 40 – 42 ― simple form of calling signal, 39, 43 – 46 ― complex form. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “ 40 – 46 ” are given under the same numbers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227530/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">
Figs. 
<number box="[972,1046,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="43.5" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="43.0">43–44</number>
</figureCitation>
), followed by low-amplitude trill sounding like monotonous buzz (the second half of the oscillogram on 
<figureCitation box="[951,1031,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 46" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[174,1423,625,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,625,1892]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 46. Macropsis validiuscula Dubovsky, oscillograms of male calling signals. 37 – 38, 40 – 42 ― simple form of calling signal, 39, 43 – 46 ― complex form. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “ 40 – 46 ” are given under the same numbers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227530/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">
Fig. 
<number box="[1003,1031,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
and the first half of the oscillogram on 
<figureCitation box="[186,266,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 46" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[174,1423,625,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,625,1892]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 46. Macropsis validiuscula Dubovsky, oscillograms of male calling signals. 37 – 38, 40 – 42 ― simple form of calling signal, 39, 43 – 46 ― complex form. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “ 40 – 46 ” are given under the same numbers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227530/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">
Fig. 
<number box="[237,266,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
) and a succession of alternating long and short pulses (
<figureCitation box="[885,969,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 46" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[174,1423,625,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,625,1892]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 46. Macropsis validiuscula Dubovsky, oscillograms of male calling signals. 37 – 38, 40 – 42 ― simple form of calling signal, 39, 43 – 46 ― complex form. Faster oscillograms of the parts of signals indicated as “ 40 – 46 ” are given under the same numbers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227530/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="108">
Fig. 
<number box="[937,969,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="108" value="46.0">46</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
